  "markup": "\u003Cp style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\u0022 class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPurpose:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E To provide eligible employees with an accrual-based bank of paid time off for various personal needs (vacation, sick leave, personal time), while acknowledging that specific details are subject to change and provided separately.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cp style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto;\u0022 class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EProcedure:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003C/p\u003E\n\u003Cul\u003E\n\u003Col start=\u00221\u0022 type=\u00221\u0022\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGeneral Purpose:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E PTO combines vacation, sick, and personal time for rest, appointments, minor illnesses, family needs, etc.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EEligibility:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E Eligibility for PTO accrual and usage is typically based on employee classification (e.g., full-time, part-time) and length of service; specifics are outlined in separate PTO documentation.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EAccrual and Usage:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E Eligible employees accrue PTO hours based on a set schedule. Requests for PTO should be submitted to your supervisor in advance through the designated system [e.g., the HR TeamIS portal]. Advance notice is generally required for planned absences (e.g., [e.g., two weeks] for vacation). Unplanned absences due to illness or emergency should follow the notification procedures outlined in the Attendance Policy. PTO usage must be approved by your supervisor, considering business needs and staffing requirements. The Company reserves the right to deny PTO requests based on business needs. PTO may not be used before it is accrued. Some states or cities may have specific paid sick leave laws that supersede or supplement this general PTO policy; Neumo will comply with all such applicable laws.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPTO at Termination of Employment\u003C/strong\u003E:\u003C/span\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E Accrued, unused PTO will be paid out upon termination of employment only where required by applicable state law. In jurisdictions where payout is not legally required, unused PTO may be forfeited upon termination.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPolicy Discretion:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E This PTO policy, including accrual rates, usage rules, and payout at termination, is subject to change at the sole discretion of Neumo, consistent with applicable laws.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003Cli class=\u0022MsoNormal\u0022 style=\u0022mso-margin-top-alt: auto; mso-margin-bottom-alt: auto; mso-list: l0 level2 lfo1; tab-stops: list 1.0in;\u0022\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EImportant Note:\u003C/strong\u003E\u003Cspan style=\u0022mso-font-kerning: 0pt; mso-ligatures: none;\u0022\u003E For the most current and comprehensive information regarding your PTO benefits, please consult with your Human Resources Business Partner or refer to the separate benefits documentation provided by the Company.\u003C/span\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\n\u003C/ol\u003E\n\u003C/ul\u003E\n\u003Cp\u003E\u0026nbsp;\u003C/p\u003E"
}]]></Value>
